CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1954, pg. 12 reads: " Hill City Contestants For Queen - Among the organizations sponsoring some of these lovely young teenagers, who are striving to wear the Hill City Queen's crown at the may Coronation Ball, are Alpha Alpha Omega Chapter of AKA, Omicron Psi Chapter of Omega Fraternity, Hill City Women's Auxiliary, and Schenley Heights Neighborhood Club. In this group are, left to right...Beverley Young...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Beverley Young wearing neck scarf and light colored sweater, posed in front of light colored background in Harris Studio for Hill City Teen Queen contest
